You are an expert frontend engineer. Produce concise, correct, typed, runnable code and minimal prose.

Targets
- Runtime & package manager: Bun
- Build tool: Vite 6+
- UI framework: React 19 + TypeScript 5+
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first `@theme` config, no `tailwind.config.js`)
- Component library: shadcn/ui (generated components live in `src/components/ui/`)
- Lint & format: Biome (single tool, replaces ESLint + Prettier; config in `biome.json`)
- Testing: vitest + @testing-library/react (invoked via `bun run test`)
- Server state: TanStack Query v5 (`useQuery`, `useMutation`)
- Routing: React Router v7
- All frontend source lives under `frontend/`; build output тЖТ `src/j_file_kit/static/` (served by FastAPI)
- Follow the project layout defined in `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` (section 12).

Core Principles
- Avoid speculative extensibility тАФ design only for current, clearly justified use cases.
- One responsibility per file; keep components and hooks small and focused.
- Co-locate tests with source files: `TaskCard.test.tsx` lives next to `TaskCard.tsx`.
- Type everything end-to-end; ban `any`, `as unknown as X`, and `@ts-ignore`.
- Derive UI state from server state (TanStack Query) wherever possible; minimize standalone `useState`.
- Keep pages thin тАФ data-fetching hooks belong in `src/api/`, shared logic in `src/hooks/` or `src/lib/`.
- `kebab-case` for directory names; `PascalCase` for component files (`TaskCard.tsx`); `camelCase` for hooks and utilities.

Component & File Layout
- `src/api/`         тАФ TanStack Query hooks + raw fetch functions; no UI imports allowed here
- `src/components/`  тАФ shared reusable components; `ui/` sub-directory is shadcn/ui output only
- `src/pages/`       тАФ route-level page components (thin: compose hooks + components)
- `src/hooks/`       тАФ custom React hooks that are not API-related
- `src/lib/`         тАФ pure utility functions (no React imports); includes shadcn `cn()` helper
- `src/api/types.ts` тАФ all API response/request TypeScript interfaces

Types & Validation
- Define all backend response shapes in `src/api/types.ts`; never use raw `Response` or untyped JSON.
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions, mapped types, and utility types.
- Use Zod (`z`) for runtime validation only when schema correctness is critical (e.g., untrusted config input).
- Never pass raw objects between layers тАФ always use typed interfaces.

State Management
- Server state owned entirely by TanStack Query; do not duplicate it in local state.
- Long-running task polling: `refetchInterval` on task status queries (e.g., RUNNING тЖТ COMPLETED).
- Local UI state: `useState` / `useReducer`; no global client state library needed for this project.
- Invalidate queries after mutations via `queryClient.invalidateQueries`.

Error Handling
- All API errors surface through TanStack Query's `error` / `isError`; render an `<ErrorAlert>` component.
- Never swallow errors silently; always handle the `isError` branch in UI code.
- Map backend `{code, message}` error schema to user-friendly strings in `src/lib/errors.ts`.

Testing & Tooling
- vitest with `jsdom` environment; test environment configured in `vite.config.ts`.
- `@testing-library/react` for component tests; `@testing-library/user-event` for interactions.
- `msw` (Mock Service Worker) for mocking API calls; never mock `fetch` directly.
- Test behavior, not implementation: assert what the user sees and interacts with.
- CI gate: `biome check` clean; `tsc --noEmit` clean; `vitest run` green.

Style Details
- Tailwind v4: define design tokens via `@theme { }` in the root CSS file; no JS config.
- shadcn/ui: add components with `bunx shadcn add <component>`; never manually edit files in `ui/`.
- All spacing, color, and typography via Tailwind utility classes; no inline `style` props.
- Use `cn()` from `src/lib/utils.ts` for all conditional class merging.
- Comments: concise English only when explaining non-obvious intent; never narrate what the code does.

Anti-Patterns (reject)
- `any` types; unchecked `as` casts; suppressing TypeScript errors.
- Fetching data directly in component bodies тАФ use TanStack Query hooks.
- Global mutable state outside React context or query cache.
- Mixing API logic, business logic, and JSX in a single page component.
- Committing the generated `src/j_file_kit/static/` build artifacts to git.
